cs.CL, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as named entity recognition. Additionally, the use of neural networks for this task suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves the use of character-level phonetics and phonology, which could fall under cs.SI (Sound and Music Computing). The use of Part-of-Speech tags as features suggests that it may also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the focus on social media data suggests that it may also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as social media data is often noisy and requires robust algorithms to handle it.
